at.tugraz.kmi.medokyservice.fca.lib.colibri.lib

Class Agenda<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • at.tugraz.kmi.medokyservice.fca.lib.colibri.lib.Agenda<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the elements stored in the agenda.

     class Agenda<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    An ordered collection that contains no duplicate elements. The order is determined by a Comparator, which is passed to the constructor. Note that the ordering implemented by the comparator must be consistent with equals. (See the Comparator interface for a precise definition of consistent with equals).

    An element can be added to the collection if it is mutually comparable to the elements that are already present in the agenda by the comparator passed to the constructor.

    The pop method returns the smallest element contained in the agenda and removes it from the agenda.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Daniel N. Goetzmann

    • Constructor Detail

      • Agenda

        Agenda(java.util.Comparator<T> c)
        Constructs an agenda whose elements will be ordered according to the order implemented by the comparator c.

        The comparator is used to order the concepts added to the agenda. For the agenda to work properly it is necessary that the objects added to it are mutually comparable, i.e. c.compare(e1, e2) must not throw an exception for any elements e1, e2 in the agenda.

        Note that the ordering implemented by the comparator must be consistent with equals. (See the Comparator interface for a precise definition of consistent with equals).

        Parameters:
        c - The comparator that will be used to compare the elements. For the agenda to work properly, the comparator must be consistent with equals (See the Comparator interface for a precise definition of consistent with equals).
